1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Thank you very much and good morning everyone

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,000
大家早上

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:10,000
I'd like to just begin with a word of prayer if we could today

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,000
我們一齊祈禱

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Heavenly Father, thank you for this time together

6
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:19,000
親愛的天父,我也多謝你,讓我們有時間一齊

7
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Thank you that we could worship you in song

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
我們用詩歌來讚美你

9
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
And now please help me and bless as we look into your word

10
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,000
求你幫助我來到去講道

11
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,000
We pray in Jesus name, Amen

12
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
奉主耶穌的名祈禱,Amen

13
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
I'm very thankful to be with you again today

14
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,000
in the Cantonese congregation at T4C

15
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:50,000
我很感恩今天可以來到你們當中和你們正道

16
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:54,000
I especially thank Pastor Har for his kind invitation to me

17
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:59,000
我特別感謝夏牧師來邀請我來到你們當中

18
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:04,000
And I also thank Betty Chan for being willing to translate for me

19
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:07,000
也多謝翻譯

20
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:11,000
On July 9th I preached a sermon here on Psalm 3

21
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,000
在7月的時候我用詩篇第3篇和大家講道

22
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
And today I would like to preach on another psalm, Psalm 13

23
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,000
今天我會來到講詩篇第13篇

24
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:29,000
This next week we will start fall semester classes at the University of Northwestern

25
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:34,000
下星期我在西北大學秋季的課程會開學

26
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:38,000
And so all this last week we had faculty meetings

27
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,000
所以上個禮拜我們有很多老師的開會

28
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:45,000
As we gathered for our meetings we prayed for one of our faculty

29
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:49,000
當我們開會的時候我們圍到其中一個老師來祈禱

30
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,000
She's on leave of absence this fall

31
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:55,000
她是暫時休假的

32
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:59,000
Last Easter doctors first discovered that her husband Scott

33
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:02,000
had an aggressive cancer in his lungs

34
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:05,000
在復活節的時候

35
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:11,000
她的先生發現有惡化的癌症

36
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:15,000
And that cancer has now quickly spread throughout his body

37
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:19,000
她的癌症很快就在她的身體裡擴散

38
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,000
They are a middle-aged couple

39
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,000
他們是中年的夫婦

40
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,000
And they have two children

41
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,000
他們有兩個小孩子

42
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:29,000
They have a daughter who is a junior in high school

43
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,000
and a son who is in 8th grade

44
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,000
她的女兒是在初中

45
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
她的兒子是八年級

46
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:41,000
At first they were counting the time the husband had left in years

47
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:45,000
他們初初的時候是在數算他丈夫史覺

48
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,000
可能還有幾年的生命

49
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,000
And they were hoping the husband would live

50
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
until the son graduated in five years

51
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:56,000
他們期望可以看到他兒子五年後畢業

52
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Then they started counting the time he had left in months

53
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:06,000
然後他們就數算他的生命只剩下幾個月

54
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
And now as his cancer becomes more aggressive

55
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,000
they are counting the time in weeks

56
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
現在他的癌症是更加的惡化

57
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:17,000
他數算他的生命是幾個星期

58
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Needless to say they are devastated

59
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:22,000
當然來說他們大家都很震驚

60
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,000
And I am sure they are wondering

61
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,000
where God is in the midst of all of this

62
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,000
我相信他們在想

63
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,000
神究竟在這件事情裡面

64
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,000
神在哪裡呢

65
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Family and friends have been praying for Scott

66
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,000
家人和朋友都為了他們來祈禱

67
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,000
And yet it seems every time

68
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,000
the doctors do an examination

69
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,000
the results are worse

70
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:47,000
而每一次他們去醫生檢查的時候

71
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,000
他們的結果都是比上一次更加差

72
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,000
And the husband's time left to live is shorter

73
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:57,000
他先生剩下來的時間是更加的短

74
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,000
So has God forgotten them

75
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,000
是不是神忘記了他們呢

76
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,000
I also know a young woman in her mid-thirties

77
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,000
我也認識一個年輕的女子

78
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,000
她大約三十多歲

79
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,000
She is faithful to God

80
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,000
and seeking to serve Him

81
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,000
她很努力的來跟隨神

82
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,000
She would like to marry

83
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,000
她很希望可以能夠結婚

84
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
And she and her family and friends

85
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
have prayed for many years

86
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
that God would bring a special man

87
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,000
into her life for her to marry

88
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,000
她的家人和她的朋友

89
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,000
都為了她這件事來祈禱

90
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:34,000
求神來將一個特別的配偶帶給她

91
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,000
But so far nothing has happened

92
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:40,000
直到現在都還沒有任何事情發生

93
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,000
And sometimes they think

94
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,000
that God has forgotten them

95
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,000
有時他們想

96
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,000
神是不是忘記了他們呢

97
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,000
And God has turned His face away

98
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,000
from their prayers

99
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,000
是不是神將他們的臉轉了

100
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
不聽他們的祈禱呢

101
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,000
I am sure we could multiply the stories

102
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,000
of people who wonder

103
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,000
if God has forgotten them

104
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,000
我相信我們可以加很多

105
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,000
其他的類似的故事

106
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,000
人在懷疑

107
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,000
神是不是忘記了他們

108
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,000
I think of older people

109
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,000
who are confined to beds in nursing homes

110
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
我想起有一些長者

111
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,000
他們在療養院的病床

112
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,000
Some of them seldom have anyone visit them

113
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:23,000
有些人是很少人來探望他們

114
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,000
And their life and strength

115
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,000
seems to be slipping away from them

116
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:30,000
他們的生命好像是慢慢的衰退

117
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,000
They sometimes feel forgotten by other people

118
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,000
有時他們覺得好像被人遺忘

119
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,000
And sometimes even forgotten by God

120
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:40,000
有時甚至他們覺得被神遺忘

121
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,000
I think of other people

122
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:44,000
who are afflicted by diseases and illnesses

123
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,000
and find no relief

124
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:50,000
有時候有些人是在病痛中找不到釋放

125
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Others have suffered irrecoverable loss

126
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:59,000
有些人是得到無法彌補的損失

127
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,000
Many such people have prayed for years

128
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,000
that God would give them relief from their problems

129
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,000
and the situation that they are in

130
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:09,000
有很多人已經為他們的處境

131
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:11,000
或者難處祈禱了很多年

132
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,000
但是得不到解脫

133
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,000
And they have not experienced

134
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,000
an answer to their prayers

135
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,000
他們得不到神的答案

136
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Has God forgotten them?

137
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,000
是不是神忘記了他們呢?

138
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:26,000
It is one thing if we as people forget

139
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,000
人是會忘記事情的

140
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,000
And we all do sometimes

141
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,000
我們很多時候都會忘記

142
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:37,000
I think of an absent-minded seminary professor

143
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:43,000
我記得有一個心不在焉的神學

144
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,000
And I'm not talking about myself here

145
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,000
這個神學教授不是我在說我自己

146
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:52,000
He went to speak in a week of meetings

147
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,000
in a church a few hundred miles from his home

148
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
他被邀請到一個地方

149
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,000
是離他家幾百里的

150
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,000
And when the meetings were over

151
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,000
he flew back to his own city

152
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:07,000
他做完講完之後

153
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,000
他回來他自己的家

154
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,000
And he took a cab to his house

155
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,000
他坐的士回到他家

156
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,000
He was greeted at the door

157
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,000
by his wife questioning him

158
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:22,000
他太太在門口迎接他

159
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,000
She asked him, "Where is the car?"

160
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,000
他問他, "你的車呢?"

161
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,000
Did you forget you drove this time?

162
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,000
你是不是忘記了

163
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:32,000
你自己開車去那個地方?

164
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Yes, he had forgotten.

165
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,000
沒錯,他忘記了

166
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,000
And he had to go back to the airport

167
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,000
and fly back to the other city

168
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,000
so he could drive his car back home.

169
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
所以他要開車回到機場

170
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:47,000
然後飛去他講到的地方

171
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,000
拿回他的車然後回家

172
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,000
It's human to forget.

173
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,000
人是會忘記的

174
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,000
But does God forget?

175
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:58,000
但是神是不是真的會忘記呢?

176
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,000
In Psalm 13, David laments the fact

177
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,000
that God has forgotten him.

178
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:07,000
在詩篇十三篇,大衛哀嘆神忘記了他

179
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:10,000
He's not asking if God has forgotten him.

180
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
他不是問神是不是忘記了他

181
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:16,000
He's charging God with forgetfulness.

182
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:20,000
他是控告神遺忘了他

183
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,000
Notice what he says

184
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:24,000
in the first two verses of Psalm 13.

185
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:30,000
我們來看詩篇十三篇第一和第二節

186
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,000
我會讀第一和第二節

187
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:35,000
耶和華說,你忘記我要到幾時呢?

188
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,000
要到永遠嗎?

189
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:40,000
你掩面不顧我要到幾時呢?

190
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,000
我心裡愁善不安

191
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,000
內心終日愁苦

192
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,000
要到幾時呢?

193
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:49,000
我的仇敵勝過我要到幾時呢?

194
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,000
Since God is eternal,

195
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:56,000
David asks if God's forgetfulness will last forever.

196
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:59,000
神是永恆的

197
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,000
大衛就問神

198
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,000
你忘記我要到幾時呢?

199
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,000
是不是要到永遠呢?

200
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Four times in these two verses

201
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:08,000
he asks God how long.

202
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,000
在這兩節聖經裏面

203
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,000
大衛是問了神四次

204
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,000
要到幾時呢?

205
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:17,000
This suggests intense frustration on his part.

206
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:22,000
我們看見大衛感受到很強烈的挫敗感

207
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,000
And his repetition of this question

208
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,000
I think is designed to motivate God to answer him.

209
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,000
他重複地問神這一句說話

210
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:34,000
是想觸動神來回答他

211
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:38,000
He can't understand why God is withholding help from him.

212
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,000
他能夠明白為何神不施予拯救呢?

213
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Especially since he is serving God.

214
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:47,000
尤其是他是服侍神的人

215
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,000
The picture in the second sentence

216
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:52,000
is that God is deliberately avoiding David.

217
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,000
在第二句那裏特別讓我們看到

218
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:59,000
神好像是故意地離開大衛

219
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,000
David is apparently forsaken by God.

220
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:05,000
大衛感受到他被神離棄

221
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,000
And he feels like God doesn't care about him.

222
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,000
神不再關心他了

223
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:14,000
Verse 2 suggests David is experiencing loneliness and sorrow day and night.

224
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:20,000
第二節那裏大衛感受到愁苦和孤單

225
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:23,000
The verse hints that he lies awake at night

226
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:27,000
trying to find some escape, some way out of his troubles.

227
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,000
每一晚他在睡覺的時候

228
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,000
他來到去籌算

229
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:36,000
想找到避難的方法

230
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,000
But when the morning light comes

231
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,000
instead of bringing hope

232
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,000
it only renews his pain.

233
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,000
當黎明的時候

234
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:46,000
他找不到解決的方法

235
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,000
並且是更加的痛苦

236
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:52,000
And he has another day of sorrow ahead of him.

237
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:58,000
而且重新又再來經歷第二天的愁苦

238
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:02,000
Then he cries himself to sleep again the next night.

239
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,000
他晚上又哭泣

240
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,000
甚至到然後才能夠入睡

241
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,000
His best plans are futile.

242
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:11,000
他最好的計劃其實都是徒然的

243
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:14,000
Any counsel he receives is worthless.

244
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,000
人家給他的忠告都是沒有用的

245
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,000
He is hurting.

246
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,000
他在受苦

247
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:22,000
And there is no way out of his grief and sorrow.

248
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:26,000
冒發是從他的悲痛和傷痛裏面走出來

249
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,000
In the last line of verse 2 he mentions his enemies.

250
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:34,000
第二節最後那裡講到他的敵人

251
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:38,000
They seem to be like circling vultures

252
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:41,000
hovering about and waiting for his fall.

253
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:44,000
那些仇敵好像那些禿頭鷹

254
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:47,000
在他的上面來賠償

255
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:50,000
等他來跌倒衰敗

256
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,000
It's likely in the original context

257
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:56,000
the enemy was someone who opposed David's kingship.

258
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,000
很可能在原文那裡

259
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:02,000
講到仇敵就是他對抗大衛的人

260
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:05,000
But verse 3 speaks of his death.

261
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:08,000
但是在第三節講到大衛的死亡

262
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:12,000
And so some people think his enemy is the physical ailment.

263
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,000
有些人就想可能他講到敵人

264
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:17,000
是不是講到他身上的病痛呢

265
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:20,000
He doesn't specify who or what his enemy is.

266
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:23,000
在經文裏面大衛沒有很清楚的指明

267
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:28,000
究竟他的敵人是病痛還是一些人

268
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:32,000
And that makes it easy for us to apply the psalm to our own situations.

269
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:37,000
所以詩篇十三篇是很容易應用在我們個人的身上

270
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:40,000
It can apply to whatever our burden is.

271
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,000
無論我們的處境我們的重擔

272
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,000
我們都可以來去應用

273
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,000
There's one other point we ought to consider

274
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,000
before we go any farther in the psalm.

275
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:52,000
我們首先來去想一下這一點

276
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:56,000
If God has forgotten David, then why does David pray to God?

277
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,000
如果神是忘記大衛的

278
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:01,000
大衛為何還要向神祈禱呢

279
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:06,000
In verses 1 and 3 he even uses the personal name for God, Yahweh.

280
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:14,000
第一節和第三節大衛甚至用耶和華這個名來呼叫神

281
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:18,000
This name refers to God as a God who relates to people

282
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,000
and makes covenants with his people.

283
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:25,000
耶和華這個字是指神是一個與人納約的神

284
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,000
亦都是與神有關係的神

285
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,000
David knows his God.

286
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,000
大衛認識這個神

287
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:36,000
Why would David use his personal name if he felt God had forgotten him?

288
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:40,000
如果大衛認為神是忘記人的神

289
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:44,000
他為何會用耶和華的名來稱呼他呢

290
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,000
Apparently deep in his heart

291
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:50,000
he realises that God actually knows about his situation.

292
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:56,000
很明顯大衛在他的心裏知道神知道他的情況

293
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:00,000
And he realises God is the only one who can deliver him from it.

294
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:06,000
他亦都了解到神是唯一的希望來幫助他解脫任何的問題

295
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,000
That's why he prays to God.

296
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,000
所以他向神祈禱

297
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:13,000
How should we respond to our suffering and misery?

298
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:19,000
我們應該怎樣去回應我們的悲痛和難處呢

299
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:23,000
Let's look at three ways that David responds in the rest of the psalm.

300
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:27,000
我們來看看大衛用了三種方法來回應

301
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:32,000
First David prays to God for help in verses 3 and 4.

302
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:38,000
首先大衛在第三節和第四節

303
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:41,000
他是向神祈禱求助

304
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,000
Let's read those verses.

305
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:46,000
我們讀第三和第四節

306
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,000
第三節

307
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:50,000
耶和華我的神啊求祢看顧我應允我

308
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:54,000
我的仇敵勝過我要到幾時呢

309
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:58,000
耶和華我的神啊求祢看顧我應允我

310
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:02,000
求祢使我的眼睛明亮免得我沉睡至死

311
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:05,000
免得我的仇敵說我勝過了他

312
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:10,000
免得我跌倒的時候我的仇敵就歡呼

313
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:13,000
In verses 1 and 2 David was lamenting.

314
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:16,000
在第一和第二節大衛是哀嘆

315
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:21,000
But in the first line of verse 3 he calls out to God to hear and answer his prayers.

316
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:27,000
在第三節大衛是呼喊神來聽他的祈禱和應允他的祈禱

317
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:30,000
He seems to be screaming out to God for help.

318
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:34,000
這個意味著他是大聲的來呼喊神

319
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:38,000
Sometimes to pray seems like simplistic and trite advice.

320
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:43,000
有時我們提議人家去祈禱好像是很簡單很平凡的提議

321
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:49,000
But true heartfelt prayer is the best thing a believer can do when hurting.

322
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:53,000
其實當一個信徒是傷心難受的時候

323
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:56,000
祈禱是最好的方法

324
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:59,000
Not only does David demonstrate faith by praying

325
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:04,000
不單止大衛是來表達他向神的信心當他祈禱

326
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:08,000
But in verse 3 he calls the Lord "my God".

327
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:11,000
他也稱呼神為"我的神"

328
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:14,000
Thus he is further confessing his trust in God.

329
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:20,000
所以我們看到他是更加的來表達他對神的信心

330
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:24,000
He knows there is only one God who can deliver him from his distrust.

331
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:31,000
他肯定只有一位神可以來拯救他的難處

332
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:39,000
In the second line of verse 3 he uses the imagery of a man who is slowly dying, perhaps on a battlefield.

333
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:43,000
在第三節第二句那裡說到一個景象

334
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:49,000
他形容一個人好像在戰場上慢慢地死亡

335
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:54,000
David says he is like a person whose life forces are fading away.

336
00:16:54,000 --> 00:17:00,000
大衛說他自己好像一個人生命力慢慢地衰退

337
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:03,000
Unless he gets help soon, he will pass away.

338
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:07,000
除非他快點得到幫助,否則他就會死亡

339
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:11,000
One commentator suggests the words "give light to my eyes"

340
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:14,000
communicate the idea of imparting new life.

341
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:18,000
有一個解經學者解釋這一句說話

342
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:23,000
他說"使我眼睛明亮"這一句說話是意指得到新的生命

343
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:28,000
Such a new life is reflected in the fresh, clear brightness of the eyes.

344
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:33,000
這個新生命從他的眼睛重新有神可以看得到

345
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:40,000
This imagery could communicate our need to have our eyes refocused on the character of our God.

346
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:48,000
這個圖畫也可以讓我們看到我們需要將我們的眼目重新定精在神的身上

347
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,000
This will restore health to our spiritual life.

348
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:56,000
是會幫助我們重建我們健康的屬靈的生命

349
00:17:56,000 --> 00:18:01,000
We are to pray to God to enlighten our eyes and give us spiritual life.

350
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:07,000
我們要向神祈禱求神給我們有新的體見,有健康的靈明

351
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:11,000
We should pray that God would give us a new perspective of himself.

352
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:18,000
我們要向神祈禱求神給我們有新的觀點,新的認識

353
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,000
We need to have our eyes refocused on the character of God.

354
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:28,000
我們需要將眼睛定精在神的身上,對他的本質有更新的認識

355
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:33,000
Because the real problem of a forgetting God is found in our view of God.

356
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:39,000
其實最大的問題,我們認為神是忘記人,其實是我們自己的問題

357
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,000
It's not his character.

358
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:43,000
不是神自己的本質出了問題

359
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:48,000
We need God to enlighten us with a true understanding of who he is.

360
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:56,000
我們需要神來幫助啟發我們明白真正認識這位神是如何的一位神

361
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:58,000
And David prays for this.

362
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,000
大衛就是這樣來祈禱

363
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:05,000
Notice also how David reasons or argues with God in verses 3 through 4.

364
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:11,000
我們亦都留意第三節和第四節,大衛怎樣從神來到理論呢?

365
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:16,000
He gives three reasons why God should answer his prayer and deliver him from his problems.

366
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:24,000
他有三個理由講給神聽,為什麼神要來聽他的祈求,英文的祈求

367
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:29,000
First, at the end of verse 3, he says if God doesn't intervene, he will die.

368
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:36,000
首先他在第三節說,神如果你不插手來干預,我就會死

369
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:40,000
He realizes he is totally dependent on God for his life.

370
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:45,000
他認定他的生命要完全依靠神,在神的手裏面

371
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:51,000
And since he is trusting in God, his situation reflects the power and faithfulness of his God.

372
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:59,000
他說他是一個信徒,所以看到他的處境是反映出神的能力

373
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:04,000
If God doesn't deliver him, it will appear as if God is weak and unfaithful.

374
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:12,000
如果神不拯救他,就會看起來好像神沒有能力去拯救他,和神是很軟弱的

375
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:16,000
There is also a second way that he seeks to motivate God to deliver him.

376
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:21,000
第二樣的論點,他用來想激勵神去救他

377
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:27,000
If God doesn't deliver him, the enemy will think he has won the victory over David and his God.

378
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:36,000
如果神不拯救大衛,他的敵人,他的仇敵就會想他們勝過了大衛

379
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:40,000
And third, he argues that his enemies will rejoice if he fails.

380
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:47,000
第三點,他的敵人就會很開心,會很歡樂

381
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,000
They will blaspheme God's name.

382
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:52,000
他們會來褻瀆神的名

383
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:57,000
I want to emphasize that we should think about our requests when we pray to God.

384
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:02,000
我想強調一點,就是當我們來向神祈求的時候

385
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,000
And we should support them with arguments.

386
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:08,000
我們應該好像大衛那樣,用一些論點來支持我們的祈求

387
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,000
That's what David does here.

388
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,000
這個就是大衛他做的方法

389
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:15,000
The saints do this throughout scripture.

390
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:19,000
聖徒在聖經裡面都是這樣做的

391
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:24,000
Job talks about doing this in Job 23, verses 3 through 4.

392
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:29,000
《約伯記》記載約伯也是這樣做

393
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:32,000
在約伯記二十三章三至四節

394
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:38,000
唯願我能知道在哪裡可以尋見神,能到他的臺前

395
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:43,000
我就在他面前將我的案件陳明滿口辯白

396
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:46,000
Moses does this in several places.

397
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:50,000
摩西在聖經裡面有幾次都是這樣做的

398
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:55,000
For example, in Numbers 14, the Israelites reject the report of the spies.

399
00:21:55,000 --> 00:22:01,000
例如在《文素記》十四章那裡,以色列人拒絕探子的回報

400
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:04,000
And they refuse to enter the land of Canaan.

401
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:07,000
他們不願意進入迦南地

402
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:10,000
So God wants to destroy the nation.

403
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:13,000
所以神就想消滅以色列民

404
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:19,000
Then Moses prays that if the Lord destroys Israel, the nations will hear about it.

405
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:26,000
所以摩西就跟神說,如果神消滅以色列民,其他萬國都會聽到,知道的

406
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:32,000
And they will say that the Lord was not able to bring the people of Israel into the land that he promised them.

407
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:40,000
他們就會說,萬國就會說,神拯救不到以色列民,帶他們進迦南地,所以就消滅了他們

408
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:44,000
And when Moses prays this, the Lord relents.

409
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:49,000
當摩西這樣向神祈禱的時候,神是留情的

410
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:52,000
And the Lord does not destroy the Israelites.

411
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:54,000
神沒有消滅到以色列民

412
00:22:54,000 --> 00:23:00,000
Instead, the Lord reaffirms the promises he had made to bring Israel into the land he promised them.

413
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:08,000
反而神是重新向以色列民來應許,帶他們進入迦南地

414
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:13,000
It brings glory to God when he keeps his promises and takes care of his people.

415
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:20,000
當神守約和來看顧他的子民的時候,是會帶給神榮耀的

416
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:23,000
We should pray for things that will bring God glory.

417
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:31,000
我們都應該同樣地為那些可以帶給神榮耀的事情來祈禱

418
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:38,000
And we should remind him that when he keeps his promises to us and delivers us, it brings glory to him.

419
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:46,000
我們應該去提醒神,當他守約看顧他的子民的時候,是會將榮耀歸給他的

420
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:51,000
In Psalm 13, David prays fervently for deliverance.

421
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:57,000
在這篇13篇,大衛很懇切地來祈求,請救

422
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:02,000
And that is how we should pray when we need God to deliver us from our agony.

423
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:08,000
我們都應該同樣地來祈禱,當我們在痛苦、憂傷裡面

424
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:12,000
David also remembers God's character in verse 5.

425
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:19,000
大衛也記得神的本性在13章5節那裡

426
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:22,000
Let's read this first.

427
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:24,000
我們讀第5節

428
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:31,000
但我倚靠你的慈愛,我的心因你的歡欣,因你的救恩快樂

429
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:37,000
This is the second thing we should do when we think God has forgotten us. Remember his character.

430
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:40,000
這個就是第二件事情我們應該要做的

431
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:45,000
當我們認為神是忘記我們的時候,我們要記得神的本性

432
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:48,000
He has prayed for a new vision of God in verse 3.

433
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:53,000
在第3節那裡,大衛向神祈禱,祈求一個新的領會

434
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:56,000
And now he has a new vision of God's character.

435
00:24:56,000 --> 00:25:01,000
神就讓他認識到神的本性

436
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,000
And his confidence is restored.

437
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:08,000
他的信心就來到去恢復了

438
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:14,000
He confidently exclaims that he is trusting in God's unfailing love.

439
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:20,000
他很有信心地宣告他倚靠神的慈愛

440
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:23,000
This is one of the most important attributes of God.

441
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:29,000
這個永不止息的愛是神其中一種最重要的屬性

442
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:32,000
It's sometimes called his steadfast love.

443
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,000
有時候可以叫做堅定的愛

444
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:40,000
It's the basis of every promise and covenant he makes with his people.

445
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:46,000
堅定的愛是神與人的應許和神與人納約的基礎

446
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:51,000
This word occurs over 250 times in the Old Testament.

447
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:56,000
堅定的愛這個字是在聖經裡面出現過250次

448
00:25:56,000 --> 00:26:00,000
And we can't understand our God until we understand this characteristic of him.

449
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:07,000
我們不能夠明白神,直到我們對這個堅定的愛有深深的體會和明白

450
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:11,000
Let's look at a few examples of this word in the Old Testament.

451
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:17,000
我們來看一下聖經裡面怎樣來講關於堅定的愛

452
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:23,000
I mentioned earlier that Moses argues with God not to destroy the Israelites in Numbers 14.

453
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:30,000
我提及文數記十四章,摩西和神爭論不可以消滅以色列民

454
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:37,000
In that situation, Moses argues with God on the basis of God's unfailing love.

455
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:44,000
在那件事情上面,摩西就是用神堅定的愛來做他的論點

456
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:48,000
Notice what it says in Numbers 14 verse 19.

457
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:53,000
我們留意文數記十四章十九節怎樣講

458
00:26:53,000 --> 00:27:03,000
求祢照祢的大慈愛赦免這百姓的罪孽,好讓祢從埃及到如今常赦免他們一樣

459
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:10,000
God had made promises to his people Israel to give them the land and to make a great nation of them.

460
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:16,000
神是給以色列民允許之地,並且令他們成為大國

461
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:22,000
And because of his steadfast unfailing love, he could not break those promises and destroy the people.

462
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:28,000
由於神堅定不變的大愛,他不可以違背他自己的承諾

463
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:36,000
In 1st Chronicles 16, when David establishes choirs in the tabernacle to sing and praise the Lord

464
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:43,000
在歷代至上十六章那裡,當大衛來到建立利美人的詩班

465
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:49,000
他在耶和華的藥櫃面前稱頌、唱詩、讚美

466
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:53,000
He does it because of the Lord's steadfast love.

467
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:57,000
他這樣做是因為耶和華的慈愛永遠長存

468
00:27:57,000 --> 00:28:00,000
Notice 1st Chronicles 16 verse 41

469
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:06,000
我們來看看歷代至上十六章四十一節

470
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:18,000
與他們一同被派的有希曼、耶稻頓和其餘所選名字錄在冊上的清謝耶和華,因他的慈愛永遠長存

471
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:23,000
The steadfast love of the Lord is the reason the Israelites sing to God

472
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:29,000
就是因為神的慈愛永遠長存,以色列人向神唱歌讚美

473
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:32,000
And it's the reason we should sing to God also

474
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:38,000
同樣我們都是因為這個原因我們來向神唱歌讚美

475
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:43,000
When Hosea buys back his adulterous wife Gomer and remarries her

476
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:52,000
當何西亞聘取他自己淫亂的妻子戈馬和他再結婚的時候

477
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:56,000
We are told that it's a picture of God's steadfast love to Israel

478
00:28:56,000 --> 00:29:04,000
我們知道這是一幅圖畫反映出神對以色列民堅定不移的愛

479
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:06,000
Notice Hosea 2.19

480
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:11,000
我們留意何西亞書2章19節

481
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:21,000
我必聘你永遠歸我為妻,以仁義、公平、慈愛、憐憫,聘你歸我

482
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:26,000
Because of his steadfast love, God cannot forsake his people

483
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:31,000
就是因為這個堅定的愛,神是不會離棄他的子民

484
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:35,000
He keeps his promises and is faithful to them

485
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:41,000
守他的約,並且永遠愛他的子民

486
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:45,000
Later today you might read Psalm 136

487
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:49,000
今天你回到家可以自己看看136篇

488
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:55,000
Every other line in Psalm 136 speaks of God's steadfast love

489
00:29:55,000 --> 00:30:02,000
詩篇136篇每一節都講到神的慈愛是永遠長存的

490
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:09,000
God's character is at stake if he should for a moment cease to care for and think of his children

491
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:21,000
如果神有任何一個時間,一刻,他不看顧他的子民或者不去愛他的子民的時候

492
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:24,000
神的誠信就會受到崩潰

493
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:27,000
Or if he would not keep his promises to them

494
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:32,000
或者他不履行他的諾言,神的誠信就會受到威脅

495
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:34,000
We are weak and helpless

496
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:37,000
人是軟弱的,是無助的

497
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:41,000
And without his steadfast love, we will fail

498
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:46,000
沒有神的慈愛來幫助我們,我們一定會失敗

499
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:53,000
But our only hope and the reason for David's confidence in Psalm 13 is the loyal love of God

500
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:59,000
在詩篇13篇裡面,大衛給我們看到他認定神就是他唯一的希望

501
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:01,000
他要依靠耶和華的慈愛

502
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:03,000
It will never fail

503
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:07,000
是永遠不會失卻的

504
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:15,000
And when David remembers God's steadfast love, the psalm changes from complaint to joy

505
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:20,000
當大衛記得耶和華的慈愛的時候

506
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:26,000
詩篇就從哀嘆變成讚美

507
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:31,000
How can we have a fresh vision of God and his character?

508
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:37,000
我們怎樣可以對神的本性或者屬性有新的體會呢?

509
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,000
We can do it through his word

510
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:42,000
我們可以通過他的話語

511
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:47,000
The Bible says that faith comes by hearing, and hearing by the word of God

512
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:52,000
聖經告訴我們,信心是從聽道而來的

513
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:58,000
Our faith will be in proportion to the degree we saturate our lives with Scripture

514
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:11,000
我們的信心的大小和聖經在我們生活裡面有多浸透的程度是成為正比的

515
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:16,000
In his trials and distress, David trusted in God's steadfast love

516
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:21,000
大衛的思念仇苦中,大衛是信靠神的

517
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:27,000
But in his time of trial, he also chose to praise God in verses 5 and 6

518
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:34,000
在第五和第六節,我們看到大衛雖然在患難中,但他仍然選擇去讚美神

519
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:36,000
Let's read those verses one more time

520
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:38,000
我們讀第五和第六節

521
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:47,000
但我依靠你的慈愛,我的心因你的救恩快樂,我要向耶和華歌唱,因他用口音代我

522
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:50,000
David began this psalm in a sob

523
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:54,000
大衛開始詩篇的時候,他是哭泣的

524
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:56,000
But he ends it in a song

525
00:32:56,000 --> 00:33:01,000
但是他結束的時候,他是歡音歌唱的

526
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:04,000
He is still not out of his distress

527
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:07,000
他仍然在他的困苦當中

528
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:12,000
But he knows that God will be faithful and one day he will be delivered

529
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:17,000
但是他知道神是信實的,有一天神會拯救他

530
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:24,000
And he knows that when he is delivered, he will complete this vow of praise to God that he is making here

531
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:30,000
當神拯救他的時候,他知道他會來到還願,來到去讚美神

532
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:35,000
For the present time, he says, my heart rejoices in your salvation

533
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:41,000
在這個時候,他就說,我的心因你的救恩歡呼

534
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:46,000
He is already rejoicing in what he knows his faithful God will do for him

535
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:51,000
他已經開始來到去歡呼,因為他知道神會來到去拯救他

536
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:59,000
And when he is delivered, he will go to the congregation and praise God in the congregation for God's deliverance of him

537
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:05,000
當神拯救他的時候,他會去到大會當中來到去重讚,讚美神

538
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:10,000
Verse 6 says, I will sing to the Lord for he has been good to me

539
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:16,000
第六節講到,我要向耶和華歌唱,因他用口音來到恩待我

540
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:19,000
David will tell the community that God delivered him

541
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:24,000
他會在大會裡面向會眾來到去見證神的拯救

542
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:28,000
Even though for a time he thought that God had forgotten him

543
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:32,000
雖然有一段時間他認為神是忘記了他

544
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:37,000
In a sense, he is praising God already when he makes this promise to God

545
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:43,000
從另一個角度來看,其實大會是在讚美神

546
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:49,000
因為他已經首先來到去認定神會拯救他

547
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:56,000
We can learn a lot from David's response to his trials and tribulations

548
00:34:56,000 --> 00:35:06,000
我們可以從大會的困境裡面,他的思念裡面來到學到很多的功課

549
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:10,000
Our appropriate response to the life that God has given us

550
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:13,000
and to his deliverance of us is praise

551
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:16,000
我們從大會身上可以學習的就是

552
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:21,000
在困境裡面我們向神來到祈禱,讚美

553
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:25,000
For the believer, praise is a matter of life and breath

554
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:32,000
對一個信徒來說,讚美就好像人呼吸一樣

555
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:35,000
Believers cannot really live without praise

556
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:39,000
我們不能夠生存如果我們不祈禱

557
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:44,000
So in Psalm 13, God gives us a picture of David's faith being stretched

558
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:48,000
by trials and testing that God brings into his life

559
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:58,000
這邊13篇,神讓我們看到一個圖畫,神藉著給大衛的試煉

560
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:05,000
幫助大衛在他的信心裡面向前邁進一步

561
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:10,000
He is so burdened by his circumstances, he thinks God has forgotten him

562
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:16,000
他在他自己處境裡面,他受到背負很重的重擔

563
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:18,000
所以他以為神是忘記了他

564
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:24,000
But he prays and God answers his prayer by giving him a fresh vision of God's steadfast love

565
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:30,000
但是他向神祈求,祈禱的時候,神幫助他對神有一個新的體見

566
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:35,000
If you are a believer, God is going to help you grow in your relationship with him

567
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:41,000
如果你是一個信徒,神將會幫助你與神有一個更親密的關係

568
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:50,000
He will do that by stretching your faith

569
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:55,000
And he will stretch your faith by allowing you to be tested and experience suffering

570
00:36:55,000 --> 00:37:01,000
他會讓你受試煉和經歷苦難,讓你的信心向前走多一步

571
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:18,000
This psalm is an example of how to cope when life is strained and you feel like God has forgotten you

572
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:22,000
In the midst of your confusion and suffering, you need to do three things

573
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:26,000
當你在迷茫中,在苦難裡面,你需要做三樣東西

574
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:31,000
Pray to God for help

575
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:37,000
Remember God's steadfast love

576
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:44,000
And vow to praise God

577
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:48,000
Let's pray together

578
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:59,000
Heavenly Father, thank you for your faithful, steadfast love for your children

579
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:07,000
If there is anyone here who doesn't know you personally

580
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:17,000
We pray they would come to you today and trust in Christ

581
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:27,000
We pray they might experience your steadfast love

582
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:39,000
And we know one way you love us is by helping us to grow

583
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:46,000
And by allowing us to have trials in our lives

584
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:54,000
We pray for those who are hurting today

585
00:38:54,000 --> 00:39:01,000
Please give them a fresh vision of your steadfast love

586
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:06,000
And strengthen their faith in you

587
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:14,000
Also turn their prayer and praise to you

588
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:21,000
When you deliver them, may it bring great glory to your name

589
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:25,000
We pray in Jesus' name, Amen

